<br>
invis is only really useful when the mage starts talking shit about how he is better dps than you becaue he has a pet and isn't completely mana dependent.  one cast and 'what pet?'<br>
<br>
as far as the group familiar idea, i really hate it.  one of the things that i like about being a wizard is the selfish nature of the class.  i consider it a trademark that none of our buffs will hit anybody but ourselves, and almost all of our aa are strictly from our benefit.  (don't start with the 'nuking benefits everbody' crap either, because i realize that.  our crits and scm though are nothing compared to stuff like MGB for benefiting other people).  i get groups well enough, and when i feel like it i have no trouble making them.  i work for myself, and my pet works for me and me alone.  no flappy of mine is gonna be some desprate group's crack dealer.<br>
<br>
one more thing: i think we would be much more powerful if it wasnt for the tanks that don't listen when you say that a mob has been rooted.  they should have sense enough to think...hmm, maybe i should get out of the way.  more and more often i find that when i announce that a mob is rooted, casters move out of the way, and tanks just stand right next to it.  i don't really know why, but they go right on doing it.  shamans seem to do the same thing with a rooted and slowed mob.  i saw one get beat to death 3 times in one group doing exactly that, as if root and slow was the same as mez.<br>
<br>
wizard crowd control is as much limited by the other people in the group not understanding how to work with wizard-controled mobs as it is by the wizard not being able to control them. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=492380" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://filebox.vt.edu/users/jomarti8/signature.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=targonis>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 795<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 12:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Back to business.</span><hr size=1> I'd love to see a spell or ability that prevents us from being summoned.  If they don't want us to use it for soloing, make it work only if we are grouped.  I for one, HATE the idea that mobs will have an innate ability like summoning characters to them.  A spell might make sense, for a god it would make sense, or a very powerful creature.  Level 51+ isn't considered powerful anymore the way it was in the original EQ.  Without mobs summoning us, our root/snare abilities would be more desired.<br>
<br>
Another idea would be to give us an AA that lowers the rate that our spells get resisted.  Wizards USED to have being resisted less as a class feature, but it's been gone a while from what I've seen.<br>
