Andrael, the point is that we already <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>have</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> group utility.  We have a surprising amount of it beyond &quot;nuke nuke nuke&quot;.  What people tend to be saying when they want group utility is &quot;I want buffs&quot;, or &quot;I want debuffs&quot;, occasionally an &quot;I want slow&quot; and then a Cedrich post with &quot;I want everything&quot;.  The way to becoming a better wizard and finding more groups isn't the addition of new abilities, it's mastery of the ones you already have- even the ones you overlook, as Natan and Quinloe do.<br>
<br>
I am deadly serious on the snare + root utility though.  If I hadn't used it, gotten good results from it, and noted it was very effective, I wouldn't stand behind it so strongly.  Judging from Natan's arguments, it doesn't seem he's ever tried this before- or at least tried it beyond any precursory attempt- and is thus knocking something he knows nothing about.<br>
<br>
