<br>
Claud, i mentioned it already... i have done exactly those things you are advertising, since a long time, because... Well beccause mainly for one reason: I couldn't keep up with the DPS and kill rate of Meleers and i wanted to contribute at least <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>something</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to the group. That were the days in Kunark, at KC for example, or Dlands.<br>
<br>
I was chain stunning Mobs, snareing them, root parking them, just because my mana would not allow me (and i was a good decked out Wizard those days too) to keep up with the group.<br>
What else is left, if you have only breeze and c1 on you (because there was nothing else out back in those days) and you can't keep up with you rmana? You stun, yeah. Great. <br>
You had to save mana, and stuns were cheap and that was all that you contributed to a group (save the occasional throwed in nuke). A conflag took 0.00001% HP of the mob away and drained 10% of your mana <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You have to accept, Claud, that the game has changed, since long actually.<br>
Groups DO NOT look for a Wizard who stuns, and parks an add, that is anyway offtanked or mezzed or not even incomming.<br>
See invis/invis DOES NOT get us into groups.<br>
Telekin DOES NOT get us into groups.<br>
Powerexodus DOES NOT get us into groups.<br>
<br>
The typical exp group these days is still exp grinding, especially in the plances Quineloe mentioned in his post.<br>
<br>
Claud, not only the game has changed, but Wizards have changed too.<br>
The only thing that has not changed is player mentality. But they see now, that Wizards can do NOW, what they were designed for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>originally</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>We can do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*now*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> sustained GREAT DPS, that is not surpassed by anyone, but maybe Mages.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Our bonus is, that Mages are often too lazy to nuke and send in only their pets... many of them are like that.)<br>
<br>
Groups DON'T want a ghetto-mezzer when they look for a Wizard. CLaud, you ever read about the grouping problem of Druids? I tend to agree with them, that they have some issues because they are generalists.<br>
<br>
If a group feels like they need serious mezzing, then they take a mezzer into their groups and don't want/expect the Wizard do mezz something.<br>
<br>
They expect us to do damage and we do it better than any Meleer these days and THIS is what gets us in groups now and this is what groups expect from Wizards.<br>
<br>
I'll give you one more example. A couple of days ago i grouped in BoT (wanted to finish my key). It was a standard pickup group, nada uber. Some people were level 62, some level 63, some level 65. Average 08/15 gear. They ooced: Group looking for a damage dealer and i asked the OOCer in tells provocantly: 'If you want DPS, take me, i provide multiple times the DPS of ANY melee class (including rogues and rangers) and i can sustain that.' He didn't want to believe me, but got intrigued, so they asked me to come.<br>
Well when i arrived there the first thing i did on the next incomming... i casted Telekin (of course resisted, hehe) when the Mob beat on the BST, our slower. I ended up tanking that Mob and just chained SOS and a draught as a finisher. (Channeling focus is so nice, heh.)<br>
Bottom line of the story: I could have saved the 300ish mana for the Telekin and just opened up with SoS (which i did then afterwards for all of the next mobs) and invest the mana in pure efficient damage than into some form of ghetto-wannabe-MIGHT-WORK-MIGHT-NOT-WORK-utility.<br>
As usual i didn't even bothered about my aggro, i had the Mobs usually after 3 second on me, but they died within 20 seconds and i barely got hit (thanks ID 5 and LR 5).<br>
<br>
But you know what? I made the test... I announced a 3 min afk, intentionally. And they kept pulling another Mob , and i was NOT doing anything that time. Result: Instead of 20 sec <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>it took them 2 minutes without me nuking to take down the Mob</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ( it's no exaggeration, it took them really 112 second, i checked, it, hehe) and their tank was SERIOUSLY hurted.<br>
Boy, they were so glad when i came back from my afk and the mobs died again within 20 sec.<br>
<br>
See what i want to tell you here, Claud? IF a Mob is dead, then you don't need to snare it, to stun it or root it, and THIS is what groups expect these days from Wizards.<br>
Groups do not care, if you can train derail something, because there ARE not trains in these days anymore. And if there are two or three mobs in the camp, then you have it either mezzed or slowed and offtank.<br>
And high AA Wizards do make very good killer-offtankers nowadays <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>(Balanz)Hmmm....very interesting. How much of this is AA, how much is runes, and how much is gear? How much is specific to <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Most comes from AA, bro. You need Quick casting, Channeling focus, ID5, LR 5 and, if possible, ND3 (to get the max out of your gear). The rest is gear of course. Heck, i never ever thought pre Pop, that int casters would be able to exceed the 6000 HP mark.<br>
Runes? No time to cast that and a waste if you cast Forceshield on yourself. (Better invest the mana in another AT or SoS.)<br>
On a standard BoT exp mob - for example,- i took (untill it was dead and boy, they die fast, perma-chaining SoS and draughts) around 200-300 damage, if things went bad i took 800 damage. (And 800 damage taken is still MUCH less then the average tank takes from them, if they have no Wiz and need 2 min untill the Mob is down instead of 20 sec.)<br>
The healer was a Druid that time, he started to gave up on the healing job and just nuked too, tossing me between the fights a small heal.<br>
<br>
The game has changed, the power of characters has changed and SOE finally got us there, where we should have been ALONG time ago:<br>
We are sufficient damage dealers and we can provide good sustained DPS. Finally. <br>
It's more fun than ever to be a Wizard and to be able to perform your role to burn stuff.<br>
<br>
The game has changed, no more pitty 50 points stuns beause you can't do anything else over the time in a chain pulling exp group. <br>
SOE got it once right, the first time, to balance Wizards properly in PoP. Thanks therefor.<br>
