<br>
    Aye, but this varies for each individual. There are a LOT of different ways to play a wizard, as you yourself said, but taking that a step further, there are some groups, as Natan pointed out, that don't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>need</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you to snare, root or stun. You talk about impressing your group with your CC abilities, but what if you're in a group that kills so fast that you never get adds? Or, in a group where none of the mobs gate, is a stun really a better idea than SOS?<br>
<br>
 With the re-introduction of the dungeon crawl in the next expansion, i think emphasis on our other abilities will come naturally. One missed snare, root or stun will probably have a good chance of ending the quest.<br>
<br>
Anyone that doesn't know how to use other options will be quickly reminded by his group the 1st time a gater isn't stunned and starts summoning them one by one. Or a runner isn't snared and brings back a train. <br>
<br>
Could we use an AE root? Doh, of course, and it would be very effective without being overpowering. Single target snare? Long overdue, also very valuable. <br>
<br>
But would this get us grouped more? No. <br>
