<br>
First off, of course you don't cast Telekin on Xegony - that's a given which I thought I put in my original post quite clearly, although I did refer to her as a hooker.<br>
<br>
Secondly, we don't usually have an overabundance of healing classes which is where stunning the trash wave (non-nameds) mobs comes in. When the assist tank calls a new target, it's often crucial that the CH has time to land - whilst other classes that can heal spots the only thing I can is to help prevent damage with Telekin which I do in those cases (Xegony and elsewhere) where the mobs have a rather high DPS even slowed and healing is scarce. Telekin is actually a nice DD as well, so DPS wise I don't lose much from using this instead of a draught - the aggro is concussionable anyway, just one concussion after a Telekin and I'm usually back and ready to nuke again. <br>
<br>
For the same reasons, Telekin comes in handy in those situations where you off-tank high level unmezzables. Since clerics are usually dealing with the MT and AEs offtankers are often left with druids/shamans as sole healing and here Telekin helps preserve their mana as well as spreading the wizard's aggro between both the main mob (decaying while you cast on add) as well as aggro on add decaying while Telekin refreshes. <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370955 target=blank>Sage Aauminki Iceblade</a><br><a href=http://www.vazaelle.dk target=blank>Caer Cadarn</a></big><br>Vazaelle Server</center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aauminki>Aauminki</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/24/03 7:07 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27003.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27003.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27003.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27003.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27003.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27003.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a> <b>7</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27003.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?t